HEADWORD: face-to-face
<hw>face-to-face</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>without
intervening persons; involving direct communication between persons in
each other's presence; -- of conversation or confrontation; <as>as,
<ex>face-to-face</ex> negotiations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> person-to-person.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having the front parts facing each other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Facette</ent>⟦br⟧
